{{Youmay|the infrared motion sensor commonly referred to as a "night scope"|[[night scope]]s, the [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] targeting [[Scope/Legends|scope]]}}
'''Infrared motion sensors''',<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> also known as '''thermal sensors''',<ref name="TOR">''[[The Old Republic]]''</ref> and commonly referred to as '''[[night scope]]s''', were [[Sensor/Legends|sensor]] devices designed to detect sources of heat and motion in near or total darkness. These sensors were used in conjunction with readout screens to display visual data for the user.<ref name="EGWT" />

Infrared motion sensors were commonly used by [[Scout/Legends|scout]] [[big game hunter]]s and [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]], though many were also favored by [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] and [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]]. The [[Ubese/Legends|Ubese]] were known to integrate infrared sensors into their battle helmets, and [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] incorporated such a device into his [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] [[Mandalorian armor/Legends|battle armor]]. Smaller versions could be fitted into one-piece [[Monocle/Legends|monocles]] and placed over a user's [[Eye/Legends|eye]]. The [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] bounty hunter [[Snoova]] was known to use such a [[Monocle ocular enhancer|device]].<ref name="EGWT" />

